Members of the Andhra Pradesh Air Travellersâ€™ Association (APATA) met Union Minister of Civil Aviation P. Ashok Gajapathi Raju recently and appealed to him to initiate steps to promote air connectivity to Visakhapatnam International Airport.APATA representatives Y. Siva Sagar Rao, Ch. Ramakotaiah, O. Naresh Kumar, D.S. Varma and Kumar Raja along with members of the Chamber of Commerce discussed with the Minister on the development of air connectivity, helicopter tourism, overnight parking of aircraft at Visakhapatnam International Airport to facilitate operation of early morning and late night flights from and to Vizag.They also appealed to the Civil Aviation Minister to consider the request of Fly Dubai to operate a daily scheduled flight from Visakhapatnam to Dubai. The Country Head of Fly Dubai S. Pran Dasan had already written to the Secretary in the Ministry of Civil Aviation on May 19, last year, seeking granting of 1,218 seats a week (one flight a day) outside the bilateral entitlements as this would advantageous to both AP and its people.The Visakhapatnam Region of APS RTC will operate around 100 Sankranti specials from Hyderabad to Visakhapatnam in view of the festival rush from January 8. The special buses to be operated include: Garuda, Super Luxury and Deluxe services. They will leave Hyderabad on January 8, 9, 10, 11, 12, 13 and 14. In the return direction, the special buses would be operated from Visakhapatnam to Hyderabad, Vijayawada and other places on January 16, 17, 18 and 19, according to Regional Manager G. Sudesh Kumar.In all, 45 specials will be operated to Hyderabad, 50 to Vijayawada, 30 to Rajahmundry, 20 to Kakinada and one additional service each to Bengaluru and Chennai.Passengers can reserve their tickets by logging on towww.apsrtconline.inor obtain them from the Dwaraka Bus Station or through authorised agents of APS RTC.Special trains will be operated by the railways between Visakhapatnam and Secunderabad and Visakhapatnam-Puri to clear the Pongal rush. Train no. 08577 Visakhapatnam-Secunderabad will leave Visakhapatnam on Jan 17 and 18 at 4.45 p.m. and reach Secunderabad on the following days at 6.15 a.m. Train no. 08578 Secunderabad-Visakhapatnam will leave Secunderabad at 5.25 p.m. on Jan 18 and 19 and arrive in Visakhapatnam at 6.50 a.m. on the following days.08478 Visakhapatnam-Puri special will leave at 7.10 a.m. on Jan 19 and 20 and reach Puri the same evening at 3.30 pm.